# =============================================================================
# EDUCATIONAL NOTES
# =============================================================================

# This configuration is designed to be educational:
# - Text files open in Ghostty terminal for learning command-line tools
# - Media files use appropriate viewers for content access
# - Archives open in file manager for extraction
# - Web content opens in browser for internet access
# - Development files open in terminal for coding workflows

# Learning tips:
# - Text files in terminal encourage command-line editing
# - Configuration files open in text editors for customization
# - Archives in file manager teach file organization
# - Development files in terminal support coding workflows

# Customization:
# - Change ghostty.desktop to your preferred text editor
# - Replace media viewers with your preferred applications
# - Add new MIME types for specialized file formats
# - Use xdg-mime command to query current associations

# Command examples:
# xdg-mime query default text/plain
# xdg-mime default ghostty.desktop text/plain
# xdg-mime install myapp.desktop